3.7.name: WebGL2RenderingContext
3.7.summary: The WebGL2RenderingContext interface provides the OpenGL ES 3.0 rendering context for the drawing surface of an HTML <canvas> element.
3.7.title: WebGL2RenderingContext

3.2.name: WebGLQuery
3.2.summary: The WebGLQuery interface is part of the WebGL 2 API and provides ways to asynchronously query for information. By default, occlusion queries and primitive queries are available.
3.2.title: WebGLQuery

3.3.name: WebGLSampler
3.3.summary: The WebGLSampler interface is part of the WebGL 2 API and stores sampling parameters for WebGLTexture access inside of a shader.
3.3.title: WebGLSampler

3.4.name: WebGLSync
3.4.summary: The WebGLSync interface is part of the WebGL 2 API and is used to synchronize activities between the GPU and the application.
3.4.title: WebGLSync

3.5.name: WebGLTransformFeedback
3.5.summary: The WebGLTransformFeedback interface is part of the WebGL 2 API and enables transform feedback, which is the process of capturing primitives generated by vertex processing. It allows to preserve the post-transform rendering state of an object and resubmit this data multiple times.
3.5.title: WebGLTransformFeedback

3.6.name: WebGLVertexArrayObject
3.6.summary: The WebGLVertexArrayObject interface is part of the WebGL 2 API, represents vertex array objects (VAOs) pointing to vertex array data, and provides names for different sets of vertex data.
3.6.title: WebGLVertexArrayObject
